Italy’s FTSE MIB Slides 1.9% as Trading Starts 6 1/2 Hours Late

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-02-22T14:33:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/italian-stocks-drop-as-trading-starts-6-1-2-hours-late-on-technical-glitch.html
Italy’s benchmark FTSE MIB Index
sank as much as 1.9 percent as trading started 6 1/2 hours late
because of “technical issues.” The gauge slid 1.8 percent to
21,821.73 at 3:31 p.m. in Milan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  